The paper deals with the problem of building a self-organized model for predicting aspects of an environment, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on an unsupervised approach for building such a model, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning known as unsupervised learning. The paper also mentions the use of Slow Feature Analysis (SFA), which is a technique commonly used in the subfield of computer vision. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of differential equations and other techniques from control- and system-theory, which are common topics in the subfield of control systems. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
